SESSION 2: HTML TEXT FORMATTING & LISTS

1. Text Formatting Tags

- <b>Text</b> → Bold text
- <strong>Text</strong> → Important bold text
- <i>Text</i> → Italic text
- <em>Text</em> → Emphasized italic text
- <u>Text</u> → Underline text
- <ins>Text</ins> → Inserted text
- <del>Text</del> → Deleted text
- <sub>Text</sub> → Subscript
- <sup>Text</sup> → Superscript

Example:

<p>This is <b>bold</b> and <i>italic</i> text.</p>

---

2. Lists in HTML

A. **Ordered List (Numbered)**

<ol>
    <li>First Item</li>
    <li>Second Item</li>
    <li>Third Item</li>
</ol>

B. **Unordered List (Bullets)**

<ul>
    <li>Apple</li>
    <li>Banana</li>
    <li>Orange</li>
</ul>

C. **Definition List**

<dl>
    <dt>HTML</dt>
    <dd>HyperText Markup Language</dd>
    <dt>CSS</dt>
    <dd>Cascading Style Sheets</dd>
</dl>

---

3. Nesting Lists

- You can put a list inside another list:

<ol>
    <li>Fruits
        <ul>
            <li>Apple</li>
            <li>Banana</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Vegetables
        <ul>
            <li>Carrot</li>
            <li>Tomato</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

---

4. Practice Tasks:

1. Create a webpage with headings and paragraphs.
2. Make an ordered list of your favorite movies.
3. Make an unordered list of your hobbies.
4. Add a definition list of 3 computer terms.
5. Try using <b>, <i>, <u>, <sub>, <sup> tags in your paragraph.

